					<h1 class="entry-title">A closer look at the Angler exploit kit</h1>
											<div class="entry-categories">
				<a href="https://news.sophos.com/en-us/category/threat-research/sophoslabs-uncut/" class="category-tag-pill">SophosLabs Uncut</a>&bull;<a href="https://news.sophos.com/en-us/category/threat-research/" class="category-tag-pill">Threat Research</a>&bull;<a href="https://news.sophos.com/en-us/tag/angler/" class="category-tag-pill">Angler</a>&bull;<a href="https://news.sophos.com/en-us/tag/drive-by-downloads/" class="category-tag-pill">Drive-by downloads</a>&bull;<a href="https://news.sophos.com/en-us/tag/exploit-kits/" class="category-tag-pill">Exploit kits</a>						</div>
					
											<div class="entry-excerpt">
							An in-depth look at one of the more notorious exploit kits used to facilitate drive-by downloads						</div>
					
